File: There have been requests for the government to gazette a list of clothing and related products that can be sold. JOHANNESBURG - The Trade and Industry department has gazetted a list of winter clothing, footwear and bedding that may be sold during level four of the lockdown. This comes after consultations with stakeholders in the textile industry. Lockdown or cough up: Offences you could be fined for There have been requests for the government to gazette a list of clothing and related products that can be sold at retail stores. The list of winter goods includes all baby and toddler clothing, maternity wear and bedding accessories. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday. Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.